Deed John Brickson et al to P. S. Lyng et al · Hot air Properties
#26981 .
THIS INDENTURE, made the 13th day of August , 1904, by and be- 1 tween JOHN ERICKSON , A. F. GUINAN, WALTER H. SODERBERG , LOTTIE MAY 1 - ·
1 PRICE, GERAULD O'SHEA, FRED GUINAN, R. L. PRICE, J. T. PRICE,
N. SODERBERG , R. B. DAWSON and EUGENE CHILBERG , parties of the first part , and R. T. LYNG, ROBERT LYNG , S. SILJAN , LEO LO WENHERZ , W. T . 1 LOVE and OLE STEN FJELD, parties of the second part ,
WITNESSETH : " That for and in consideration of the sum of One ( $1.00) Dollar, in hand paid by said parties of the second part , to said parties of the first part , the receipt whereof is hereby a cknowl- edged, and in consideration of a full and complete settlement of all suits now existing between said parties of the first part and said parties of the second part , or any of them, + and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt whereof is hereby acknowledged, the said parties of the first part have , and by these presents do grant, bargain, selland convey unto the said parties . of the Second part, and to their heirs and assigns forever, the follow ing described mining claims situate and being on the Right Limit of . Glacier Creek, in the Cape Nome Mining District, District of Alaska , and more particularly described as follows, to-wit :
That mining location known as the Johansen or Columbia Claim , also the mining location known as the Fredericks Claim, also that cer- tain fraction known as the Johnston Fraction, and also that certain fraction known as the Surprise Fraction, said properties being known as the Hot Air Mining Claim, and being the same properties as are more particularly described on pages three and four in the complaint in the case of Alfred Nilima and Ole Stenfjeld, plaintiffs, against John Erick son , A. F. Guinan , Lottie May Price , W. H. Soderberg, Chas.D.Lane , R. B. Dawson , N . Soderberg, Fred Guinan, and Eugene Chilberg, defend- ants, in action numbered 1150, in the United States District Court in and for the District of Alaska, Second Division, which descriptions by reference thereto, are made a part of this description .
·
Also the dumps and all gravel, and gold contained therein, now situate and located on said properties or upon the claim or claims ʻ adjacent thereto and particularly on the location known as the Utica Claim or location, which said dumps have been extracted from the Hot Air Mining Claim, also the right to use said Utica Claim as a dumping
167
ground for any and all, tailings taken, or to be taken from any of the mining claims aforesaid , until all mining operations on the same shall have been completed and until said properties as workable mining properties shall be ex- huasted, together with the right to re-handle and extract the gold in and from said dumps, carrying on said re-handling operations upon said Utica Claim, useing it for said purpose , and also as a dumping ground for the tailings from the dumps so re-handled as aforesaid, provided seid dumping privilege shall not extend beyond 300 feet from the upper end of said Utica Claim unless necessary .
TOGETHER with all and singular the tenements, hereditaments and appur- tenances, thereunto belonging or in anywise appertaining, and the reversion and reversions , remainder and remainders, rents, issues and profits thereof, subJect to rights expressed in contract of even date herewith executed by W .T . Love et - al to John Erickson et al for the payment of twenty-five per cent . of the gross output of said mine until $50,000 is paid .
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD all and singular the said premises, together with the appurtenances unto the said parties of the second part and to their heirs and assims forever, to each of said second parties in the same proportion as his interest may appear to be in the action hereto fore pending in the United States District Court in and for the District of Alaska , Second Division, entitled Alfred Nilima , Ole Stenfjeld and Oliver Oleson , plaintiffs, against . Geo . A. Shea , as Administrator of the Estate of J. P. Johansen , deceased, et al, defendants, being cause Numbered 431, in said District Court .
The said parties of the first part hereby agree to deliver to said part- ies of the second part quiet peaceable and exclusive possession of the mining property aforesaid, and to thereafter in no manner interfere with the title or , possession of said parties of the second part .
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the said parties of the first part have hereunto set their hands and seals the day and year first above written.
In presence of :-
J. T. Price : R.L.Price , By J . T. Price, Atty in fact.
Albert Fink . ·
John L. McGinn >
